{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888094130,"sessionID":"ses_284d26f6cffep1c53tLhzWJxzP","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2dd3840014N8GMoIZjGXzdh","messageID":"msg_d7b2db5b4001wpU2u6V7tupQEy","sessionID":"ses_284d26f6cffep1c53tLhzWJxzP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7971340d59e04164b421e724cbb99574","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module**: `manifests`\n4: **Language**: YAML\n5: **Size**: M\n6: **Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n7: \n8: ## Task Breakdown\n9: \n10: ### Task 1: Review existing Workload Manager ServiceAccount template\n11: - [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n12: - [ ] Verify template includes proper Helm conditionals (enabled and serviceAccount.create)\n13: - [ ] Verify template uses correct helper functions (serviceAccountName, namespace, labels)\n14: - [ ] Verify component label is set to workload-manager\n15: - [ ] Verify annotations are conditionally included\n16: - [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n17: \n18: **Verification**: Template follows best practices and matches component pattern\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ### Task 2: Review existing Workload Manager RBAC template\n23: - [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n24: - [ ] Verify ClusterRole is defined with proper metadata\n25: - [ ] Verify ClusterRoleBinding is defined with proper metadata\n26: - [ ] Verify rules reference .Values.rbac.clusterRole.rules\n27: - [ ] Verify subjects reference correct ServiceAccount\n28: - [ ] Verify roleRef references correct ClusterRole\n29: - [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n30: \n31: **Verification**: Template matches delta-spec.md requirements for Workload Manager\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### Task 3: Complete Workload Manager ClusterRole rules in values.yaml\n36: - [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/values.yaml rbac.clusterRole.rules section\n37: - [ ] Verify rules include permissions for agent-sandbox resources\n38: - [ ] Verify rules include permissions for AgentRuntime CRDs (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes)\n39: - [ ] Verify rules include permissions for CodeInterpreter CRDs (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters)\n40: - [ ] Verify rules include permissions for status subresources\n41: - [ ] Verify rules include permissions for core workloads (pods, services, configmaps)\n42: - [ ] Verify rules include permissions for secrets (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete)\n43: - [ ] Verify rules include permissions for events (create, patch)\n44: - [ ] Verify rules follow principle of least privilege (no wildcards unless necessary)\n45: - [ ] Add any missing permissions based on delta-spec.md requirements\n46: \n47: **Verification**: Workload Manager ClusterRole has all required permissions with minimal privileges\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### Task 4: Review existing Controller Manager ServiceAccount template\n52: - [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n53: - [ ] Verify template includes proper Helm conditionals\n54: - [ ] Verify template uses correct helper functions\n55: - [ ] Verify component label is set to controller-manager\n56: - [ ] Verify annotations are conditionally included\n57: - [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n58: \n59: **Verification**: Template follows best practices and matches component pattern\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ### Task 5: Review existing Controller Manager RBAC template\n64: - [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n65: - [ ] Verify Role is defined with proper metadata\n66: - [ ] Verify RoleBinding is defined with proper metadata\n67: - [ ] Verify rules reference .Values.controllerManager.rbac.rules\n68: - [ ] Verify subjects reference correct ServiceAccount\n69: - [ ] Verify roleRef references correct Role\n70: - [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n71: \n72: **Verification**: Template matches delta-spec.md requirements for Controller Manager\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ### Task 6: Define Controller Manager Role rules in values.yaml\n77: - [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/values.yaml controllerManager.rbac.rules section\n78: - [ ] Define rules for managing AgentCube CRDs (agentruntimes, codeinterpreters)\n79: - [ ] Define rules for watching and updating resources\n80: - [ ] Define rules for creating and managing sub-resources (configmaps, secrets, events)\n81: - [ ] Define rules for status subresources\n82: - [ ] Ensure rules are namespace-scoped (no cluster-wide permissions)\n83: - [ ] Follow principle of least privilege\n84: - [ ] Add rule for getting and updating pods status\n85: - [ ] Add rule for creating events\n86: \n87: **Verification**: Controller Manager Role has all required permissions with minimal privileges\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ### Task 7: Review existing Router ServiceAccount template\n92: - [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n93: - [ ] Verify template includes proper Helm conditionals\n94: - [ ] Verify template uses correct helper functions\n95: - [ ] Verify component label is set to router\n96: - [ ] Verify annotations are conditionally included\n97: - [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n98: \n99: **Verification**: Template follows best practices and matches component pattern\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ### Task 8: Review existing Router RBAC template\n104: - [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/rbac.yaml\n105: - [ ] Verify Role is defined with proper metadata\n106: - [ ] Verify RoleBinding is defined with proper metadata\n107: - [ ] Verify rules i